        "evidence": "<p>Total plasma dosage, mL = desired plasma dosage, mL/kg &times; weight, kg</p>\n<p>Note the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Desired plasma dosage ranges from 10 to 20 mL/kg.</li>\n<li>This dose is expected to increase the level of coagulation factors by 20% immediately after infusion.</li>\n<li>A recommended standard dose of FFP is 10 mL/kg, but doses up to 15 or 20 mL/kg may be justified based on the clinical situation.</li>\n</ul>",
